    "script_type": "Abugida (alphasyllabary) - each character represents a consonant-vowel combination",
    "word_order": "SOV (Subject-Object-Verb)",
    "notable_features": [
      "Written in the ancient Ge'ez script, shared with Amharic and Tigre",
      "Gendered language: masculine and feminine nouns, with verb agreement",
      "Verb-final word order (SOV), unlike most other Semitic languages (which are SVO/VSO)",
      "Rich verb morphology with consonantal root system (typically 3 consonants)",
      "First appeared in writing during the 13th century"
